    <h2>Engineered Learning</h2>
    <p>It’s rare when a company whose product we use approaches us to collaborate. You can imagine our excitement when Meteor wanted us to design & engineer their learning materials. We were tasked with conceiving example applications that would pique curiosity and serve as reference material.</p>

    <p>Example apps exist at the junction between acquisition and engagement. Once users express interest in Meteor we further engage them with examples that address their real-life use cases and illuminate common development patterns. We started with concrete requirements: illuminate essential framework concepts, showcase layout patterns, and define best practices for app structure. Next we identified use cases where Meteor could add tremendous value like social engagement, list-keeping, and game scoring. It was important to balance information and inspiration to show that great experiences were easily achievable with Meteor.</p>
  </div>
</div>

