    <h2>Meteor Fundamentals</h2>
    <p>People are often incredulous when discovering how intuitively Meteor solves common challenges. One such challenge is ensuring that all connected users see the latest data. For example, a score page of game should always reflect the current score and not need to update data via a page reload. In the request-response world of Rails and PHP building realtime functionality is not trivial. With Meteor's leaderboard example we not only prove it can be done elegantly.</p>

    <h2>Assembling an App</h2>
    <p>Todo apps are classic coding exercises. It was important to combine the simple patterns from the leaderboard example into a cohesive whole. Our objective was to illustrate the ease of assembling a real web app by combining basic features.</p>


    <p>Common features of modern apps are responsive layouts, individual user accounts, and the ability to collaborate. A responsive app is able to transition from large to small screens with ease. User accounts help keep track of several lists at once. Collaboration gets more people involved in the product. We combined these pieces into a collaborative todo list that syncs private lists seamlessly across any device.</p>
  </div>
</div>

